      "exp_en": "The best answer is \"an IDH-mutant grade 2-3 astrocytoma with CDKN2A/B homozygous deletion is classified as astrocytoma, IDH-mutant, WHO grade 4.\". The key teaching point for \"IDH-mutant molecular upgrade\" is: an IDH-mutant grade 2-3 astrocytoma with CDKN2A/B homozygous deletion is classified as astrocytoma, IDH-mutant, WHO grade 4.. The distractors may be true statements from the same chapter, but they do not answer the specific concept being asked.",
      "A": "若 IDH 突變型第 2-3 級星形膠質細胞瘤具有 CDKN2A/B 同型合子缺失，則分類為 IDH 突變型星形膠質細胞瘤，WHO 第 4 級。",
      "A_en": "an IDH-mutant grade 2-3 astrocytoma with CDKN2A/B homozygous deletion is classified as astrocytoma, IDH-mutant, WHO grade 4.",
      "ans": "A",
      "B": "若 IDH 突變且有 1p/19q 共同缺失，走向少突膠質細胞瘤；若 IDH 突變但沒有 1p/19q 共同缺失，且有 ATRX 缺失或 TP53 突變，走向星形膠質細胞瘤。",
