      "B_en": "The first step in glioma management is usually maximal safe resection, with the goal of removing as much tumor as possible while preserving neurologic function. For deep-seated, eloquent, or multifocal tumors, subtotal resection, debulking, or stereotactic biopsy may be appropriate.",
