      "exp": "正確答案是「Symptomatic radiation necrosis 的 first-line treatment 是 corticosteroids，例如 dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day 並 gradual taper。其他選項包括 bevacizumab、pentoxifylline + vitamin E；投影片列出 Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU BID ×6 months。」。本題考的是「腦轉移」的核心原則：Symptomatic radiation necrosis 的 first-line treatment 是 corticosteroids，例如 dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day 並 gradual taper。其他選項包括 bevacizumab、pentoxifylline + vitamin E；投影片列出 Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU BID ×6 months。。其他選項本身可能是同章節的另一個真實重點，但不是本題所問的核心概念。",
      "exp_en": "The best answer is \"First-line treatment for symptomatic radiation necrosis is corticosteroids, such as dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day with gradual taper. Other options include bevacizumab and pentoxifylline + vitamin E; the slides list Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU twice daily for 6 months.\". The key teaching point for \"Brain Metastases\" is: First-line treatment for symptomatic radiation necrosis is corticosteroids, such as dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day with gradual taper. Other options include bevacizumab and pentoxifylline + vitamin E; the slides list Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU twice daily for 6 months.. The distractors may be true statements from the same chapter, but they do not answer the specific concept being asked.",
