      "exp_en": "The best answer is \"The advantage of WBRT is treatment of macroscopic and microscopic disease throughout the whole brain, improving intracranial control; the disadvantage is neurocognitive decline at 4-6 months, especially delayed recall and short-term memory.\". The key teaching point for \"Brain Metastases\" is: The advantage of WBRT is treatment of macroscopic and microscopic disease throughout the whole brain, improving intracranial control; the disadvantage is neurocognitive decline at 4-6 months, especially delayed recall and short-term memory.. The distractors may be true statements from the same chapter, but they do not answer the specific concept being asked.",
      "A": "Symptomatic radiation necrosis 的 first-line treatment 是 corticosteroids，例如 dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day 並 gradual taper。其他選項包括 bevacizumab、pentoxifylline + vitamin E；投影片列出 Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU BID ×6 months。",
      "A_en": "First-line treatment for symptomatic radiation necrosis is corticosteroids, such as dexamethasone 4-8 mg/day with gradual taper. Other options include bevacizumab and pentoxifylline + vitamin E; the slides list Trental 400 mg + Vitamin E 400 IU twice daily for 6 months.",
      "B": "也常出現在 arterial circulation 的 terminal watershed areas。分布大致隨腦部重量與血流:約 80% cerebral hemispheres、15% cerebellum、5% brainstem。",
      "B_en": "they also commonly occur in terminal watershed areas of arterial circulation. Distribution roughly follows brain weight and blood flow: about 80% in cerebral hemispheres, 15% in the cerebellum, and 5% in the brainstem.",
      "C": "WBRT 的優點是治療 whole brain macroscopic + microscopic disease，改善 intracranial control；缺點是 4-6 個月後的 neurocognitive decline，尤其 delayed recall / short-term memory。",
      "C_en": "The advantage of WBRT is treatment of macroscopic and microscopic disease throughout the whole brain, improving intracranial control; the disadvantage is neurocognitive decline at 4-6 months, especially delayed recall and short-term memory.",
      "ans": "C",
      "D": "SRS alone cognition better, OS generally similar, but local/distant brain failure higher；WBRT 則 intracranial control better, cognition worse, OS usually not improved。",
      "D_en": "SRS alone has better cognition and generally similar overall survival, but higher local and distant brain failure; WBRT has better intracranial control, worse cognition, and usually no overall-survival improvement."
