      "stem_en": "Which description of \"Palliative RT\" is most accurate?",
      "exp": "正確答案是「Radiation emergency 不等於一定要立刻 RT。核心原則是:先評估是否真正急危、是否需要 tissue diagnosis、是否有 prior RT、是否需要先手術/介入處置。」。本題考的是「緩和放射治療」的核心原則：Radiation emergency 不等於一定要立刻 RT。核心原則是:先評估是否真正急危、是否需要 tissue diagnosis、是否有 prior RT、是否需要先手術/介入處置。。其他選項本身可能是同章節的另一個真實重點，但不是本題所問的核心概念。",
      "exp_en": "The best answer is \"A radiation emergency does not automatically mean immediate radiotherapy. The first step is to decide whether the situation is truly urgent, whether tissue diagnosis is needed, whether the patient has had prior radiotherapy, and whether surgery or an interventional procedure should come first.\". The key teaching point for \"Palliative RT\" is: A radiation emergency does not automatically mean immediate radiotherapy. The first step is to decide whether the situation is truly urgent, whether tissue diagnosis is needed, whether the patient has had prior radiotherapy, and whether surgery or an interventional procedure should come first.. The distractors may be true statements from the same chapter, but they do not answer the specific concept being asked.",
      "A": "MSCC suspected 時 first step 是 steroids，作為 definitive treatment 前的 bridge。Mechanism 是減少 inflammation 與 cord edema，並對 multiple myeloma/lymphoma 有 direct oncolytic effects。要 monitor hyperglycemia、hypertension，並用 PPI 或 H2 blocker 做 GI prophylaxis。",
      "A_en": "When MSCC is suspected, the first step is steroids as a bridge to definitive treatment. Steroids reduce inflammation and cord edema and may have direct oncolytic effects in multiple myeloma and lymphoma. Monitor hyperglycemia and hypertension, and provide gastrointestinal prophylaxis with a PPI or H2 blocker.",
      "B": "Radiation emergency 不等於一定要立刻 RT。核心原則是:先評估是否真正急危、是否需要 tissue diagnosis、是否有 prior RT、是否需要先手術/介入處置。",
      "B_en": "A radiation emergency does not automatically mean immediate radiotherapy. The first step is to decide whether the situation is truly urgent, whether tissue diagnosis is needed, whether the patient has had prior radiotherapy, and whether surgery or an interventional procedure should come first.",
      "ans": "B",
      "C": "Cord compression 定義是任何 radiographic compression of spinal cord 或 cauda equina。可分 epidural compression，由 tumor 或 bone fragment 造成；intradural disease；intradural extramedullary，例如 leptomeningeal disease；intramedullary，即 spinal cord 內 tumor deposit。",
      "C_en": "Cord compression is any radiographic compression of the spinal cord or cauda equina. It can be epidural compression from tumor or bone fragment, intradural disease, intradural extramedullary disease such as leptomeningeal disease, or intramedullary tumor deposit within the spinal cord.",
      "D": "急性 airway compromise 先 bronchoscopy/stent/laser; 穩定後控制 hemoptysis、cough、dyspnea; 10 Gy ×1、17 Gy/2、20 Gy/5、30 Gy/10、40-45 Gy/15",
